Claude Code Hooks - Complete Reference
Hook Types Available
Hook Event	Trigger
PreToolUse	Before a tool executes
PostToolUse	After a tool completes
Notification	System notifications
UserPromptSubmit	When user submits a prompt
SessionStart	When session begins
SessionEnd	When session ends
Stop	When Claude stops execution
SubagentStart	When subagent starts
SubagentStop	When subagent stops
PreCompact	Before context compaction
PermissionRequest	When permission is requested
Hook Configuration Schema
{
  "hooks": {
    "PostToolUse": [
      {
        "matcher": "Bash",
        "hooks": [
          {
            "type": "command",
            "command": "echo 'Tool completed'",
            "timeout": 30,
            "statusMessage": "Running post-tool check..."
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
    "Stop": [
      {
        "hooks": [
          {
            "type": "command",
            "command": "/path/to/script.sh",
            "timeout": 60
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  }
}
Three Hook Types
1. Command Hook
{
  "type": "command",
  "command": "jules remote list --session | head -5",
  "timeout": 30,
  "statusMessage": "Checking Jules status..."
}
2. Prompt Hook
{
  "type": "prompt",
  "prompt": "Analyze this output and summarize: $ARGUMENTS",
  "timeout": 60,
  "model": "claude-sonnet-4-5-20250929"
}
3. Agent Hook
{
  "type": "agent",
  "prompt": "Verify that the operation completed successfully. $ARGUMENTS",
  "timeout": 60,
  "model": "claude-sonnet-4-5-20250929"
}
